node.text:
Today the @afthunderbirds flew over Front Range communities to honor health care workers, first responders, military members and other essential personnel who are working on the front lines to combat Covid-19. Here is the moment the Thunderbirds flew over downtown Denver this afternoon. It was beautiful!! Did you see the flyover from your house today? Video credit: @9newsdenver

PHOTO CONTEST 📷 for 2 VIP tickets to the Westword Music Showcase this Saturday 9/18 🎶 🎸🎹🎤😆

We have two VIP tickets to give one luck follow. Here’s how to enter:

1. Submit your best past Westword Music Showcase pics using the hashtag #wms_vip 👈🏼
2. Unlimited entries. Photos must have been captured by you at a past Westword Music Showcase Concert.
3. That’s it. One winner will be selected this Thursday night. Good luck! 🤘

#MileHighHappenings September 2021. August literally happened in the blink of an eye! We loved seeing you all out and about enjoying live music, art festivals, breweries, and much more. September is sure to bring a different vibe to the Mile High City, with lots of food themed events and (hopefully) cooler temps prepping you for hibernation. node.text:
#Regram @fivepointsatlas: Park Hill Day of Legends honors local leaders on Black Philanthropy Day with a Community Day Party.

DENVER—The Park Hill Pirates are hosting an end fall camp celebration honoring local Park Hill community legends on Black Philanthropy Day, August 28. This dynamic event champions the Park Hill Legacy while taking pride in living, serving and supporting the valued assets within the Park Hill Community.

The Park Hill Pirates Day of Legends creates a true community engagement opportunity in which the entire community (kids, parents, guardians, volunteers, alumni, supporters, partners, businesses, etc) can create, build, foster and maintain connections beyond the day’s activities. In addition, continue to acknowledge and celebrate those that have significantly impacted the community through annual Leadership and Legacy Awards.

This community gathering features scrimmages for each team/age group, cheerleaders to performances in front of a crowd, and the presenting of our awards. Activities include a kid zone with bouncy castles, face painting, crafts and more. The day party will include DJs, food trucks and over 50 vendors and partners.

We anticipate over 1,500 people connecting throughout the event.

WHAT: Park Hill Day of Legends community celebration & Black Philanthropy Day
WHERE: Skyland Park (5600 E. 35th Avenue Denver, CO, 80207)
WHEN: Saturday, August 28th, 9am - 5pm MST | Day Party Noon - 5pm MST
